case_circumstances: Body was found in the attic area of a burning abandoned house by fire department personnel.
case_head_hair:
A black wig with straight coarse hair was found with the victim, it is unknown if this relates to the unknown individual as much debris was found in the area of the scattered remains.
Dark brown, relatively fine and slightly wavy human hairs found at the scene are assumed to belong to this individual.
case_eye_description: Eye color could not be determined due to decomposition.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: Blue jeans found may be associated to this individual. Although badly burned, they appear to be a size 16.
case_footwear: Pair of black or dark blue sneakers, B.U.M. Equipement brand, size 7 were found with the debris and may or may not be associated to the unknown individual.
case_other_items_with_body: Silver metal hair clasp or barrette 5mm wide and 6cm long was attached to the wig found at the scene.
dental: Dental information / charting is available and will be entered later
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
